Dear colleagues,

Due to	numerous requires, paper submission deadline for MCO'08 conference
(http://lita.sciences.univ-metz.fr/~mco08/) is extended to May 29, 2008. This
deadline is a hard deadline due to the organization of the printing of the
proceedings and there will be NO exception at all.

To be included in the conference proceedings, each accepted paper requires one
full registration, i.e., at least one co-author is fully registered with
payments by the deadline to ensure the presence at the conference. The
registration page of our website will be available very soon.

As a reminder for the submission:
1. LNCS format shall be strictly applied.
2. The LNCS electronic author kit is made available on LNCS website, and is
linked from the submission page of our website.
ftp://ftp.springer.de/pub/tex/latex/llncs/latex2e/instruct/
3. If you want to submit your paper on a special session or workshop, 
please inform us adding a comment to the chair when completing the
submission form.

For further informations, please visit our website :
http://lita.sciences.univ-metz.fr/~mco08/

You may be advised of the important dates :

Paper Submission :		      May 18, 2008, extended to May 29,
2008
Author Notification :		      June 15, 2008
Early registration :		      July 5, 2008
Last version of accepted papers :     July 5, 2008 (new date)
Conference Dates :		      September 8 to 10, 2008
Paper submission to special issues :  November 30, 2008


Thank you in advance and hope to see you during the conference.


Organizing committee of MCO'08

